HEADWORD: AAAS
<hw>AAAS</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the <org>American
Association for the Advancement of Science</org>, an organization with
headquarters in Washington, D.C. Its goal is to advance the physical and
social sciences, and it publishes a weekly journal <jour>Science</jour>,
with original research articles as well as reviews and commentary.</def>
<mark>[Acronym.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <org>American Association for the Advancement of
Science</org>.</syn>
